        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 1 at 3:41PM EDT by NWS Greenville-Spartanburg SC</headline>
        <description>At 341 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 7
miles north of Mocksville, or 5 miles southeast of Courtney, moving
southeast at 10 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Farmington and Sheffield.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
